gurmukhi: ਜੈਸੇ ਪਾਂਚੋ ਤਤ ਬਿਖੈ ਬਸੁਧਾ ਨਵਨ ਮਨ ਤਾ ਮੈ ਨ ੳੁਤਪਤ ਹੁੲਿ ਸਮਾਤ ਸਭ ਤਾਹੀ ਮੈ
transliteration: Jaisay Paancho Tat Bikhai Basudhaa Navan Mana , Taa Mai N Outapat Hui Samaat Sabh Taahee Mai ?
translation: Just as Earth is most humble out of the five elements. That is why it produces so much and all that goes back to it.

gurmukhi: ਜੈਸੇ ਪਾਂਚੋ ਅਾਂਗੁਰੀ ਮੈ ਸੂਖਮ ਕਨੁੰਗ੍ਰੀਅਾ ਹੈ ਕੰਚਨ ਖਚਤ ਨਗ ਸੋਭਤ ਹੈ ਵਾਹੀ ਮੈ
transliteration: Jaisay Paancho Aanguree Mai Sookham Kanoungreeaa Hai , Kanchan Khachat Nag Sobhat Hai Vaahee Mai ?
translation: Just as the little finger of the hand is smallest and frail looking, yet a diamond ring is worn in it.

gurmukhi: ਜੈਸੇ ਨੀਚ ਜੋਨ ਗਨੀਅਤ ਅਤਿ ਮਾਖੀ ਕ੍ਰਿਮ ਹੀਰ ਚੀਰ ਮਧੁ ੳੁਪਜਤ ਸੁਖ ਜਾਹੀ ਮੈ
transliteration: Jaisay Neech Jon Ganeeat Ati Maakhee Krima , Heer Cheer Madhu Oupajat Soukh Jaahee Mai ?
translation: Just as fly and other insects are counted among the low species, yet some of them produce such valuable things like silk, pearls, honey etc;

gurmukhi: ਤੈਸੇ ਰਵਿਦਾਸ ਨਾਮਾ ਬਿਦਰ ਕਬੀਰ ਭੲੇ ਹੀਨ ਜਾਤ ੳੂਚ ਪਦ ਪਾੲੇ ਸਭ ਕਾਹੀ ਮੈ ||੬੩੨||
transliteration: Taisay Ravidaas Naamaa Bidar Kabeer Bhaay , Heen Jaat Ooch Pad Paaay Sabh Kaahee Mai ?632?
translation: Similarly, saints like Bhagat Kabir, Namdev Ji, Bidar and Ravi Das Ji being low born have attained a much higher spiritual level who have blessed humanity with their precept that have made their life peaceful and comfortable.
